			<footnote ID="I77eccab074d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">
				<label.designator>5</label.designator>
				<footnote.body>
					<para>
						<bop/>
						<bos/>
						<paratext>In <cite.query w-src-number="0287018130" w-serial-number="1978132486" w-seq-number="00007" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000711" ID="Ic29cc6b274d211eab2f0b920da2605c5">State v. Trippe, 146 Ga. App. 210, 246 S.E.2d 122 (1978)</cite.query>, the Georgia Court of Appeals affirmed the trial court&apos;s motion to suppress on the ground that a school security officer, who was also a special deputy sheriff, was acting as a law enforcement officer as he assisted school personnel in the dormitory search.<eos/>
						</paratext>
						<eop/>
					</para>
				</footnote.body>
